The '''''Corellia Times''''', or '''''Corellian Times''''', was a [[NewsNet]]<ref name="GNN3" /> and newspaper based in [[Coronet City/Legends|Coronet]] on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]] before and during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="SWG:CSV" />

==Description==
[[File:Corellia_times_building.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The ''Corellia Times'' building in Coronet]]
The ''Corellian Times'' was a [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] news agency and one of the major financial [[NewsNet]]s. Its main focus was on covering business and financial news and reporting.<ref name="GNN3" /> However, the newspaper also covered more traditional topics, such as criminal affairs,<ref name="SWG:CSV" /> social events,<ref name="CTELDR" /> or galactic exploration.<ref name="SWG:ToOW">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan]]''</ref>

==History==
During the last decade of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]],<ref name="TQC">{{SonyCite|url=players/news_archive.vm?id=68410&month=082009|text=Friday Feature &ndash; The Quest Continues}}</ref> the ''Corellia Times'' reporter [[Horace Korr]] covered the kidnapping and murder of [[Felicia]] Covington on [[Rori/Legends|Rori]].<ref name="SWG:V" />

During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Period]], the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] supported the ''Corellia Times'' in order to limit the publication of its [[Alien/Legends|non-Human]] rival, the [[Herglic Trading Journal]], another major financial NewsNets.<ref name="GNN11">{{JournalCite|11|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], some of its employees were [[Finn Shallo]],<ref name="SWG:CSV" /> [[Hol't Deb Orah]],<ref name="CTELDR" /> [[Ista Kezever]],<ref name="BV">{{SonyCite|url=content.jsp?page=Broken%20Viewscreen|text=The Broken Viewscreen, or How to Save a Picture Forever}}</ref> [[Jural]],<ref name="SWG:ToOW" /> [[Halden Wes]],<ref name="SWG:MtM">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Muddle the Meatlumps|Corellia}}</ref> [[Vani Korr]],<ref name="SWG:HVKItM">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Help Vani Korr Investigate the Meatlumps|Corellia}}</ref> and [[Marles Jacobe]].<ref name="SWG:C1">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=other}}Chapter 1: The Battle for Restuss</ref>

After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], the ''Corellia Times'' covered the [[Life Day/Legends|Life Day]] events in [[Dearic/Legends|Dearic]], [[Wayfar/Legends|Wayfar]], and [[Doaba Guerfel/Legends|Doaba Guerfel]].<ref name="CTELDR" /> In the meantime, Vani Korr investigated the criminal organization known as the [[Meatlumps]] and wrote the article "[[Who are the Meatlumps?]]," which was published in the ''Corellia Times''.<ref name="SWG:HVKItM" /> Around the same time, Ista Kezever published "[[The Broken Viewscreen, or How to Save a Picture Forever]]," an article about the repair of [[Viewscreen/Legends|viewscreens]].<ref name="BV" /> Marles Jacobe later covered the [[Battle of Restuss]], on [[Rori/Legends|Rori]].<ref name="SWG:C1" />

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], ''Corellia Times'' covered the relocation of the [[Gowix Computers]] company from Corellia to [[Corulag/Legends|Corulag]].<ref name="GNN7">{{JournalCite|7|Galaxywide NewsNets}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The ''Corellia Times'' was first mentioned in the "[[Galaxywide NewsNets]]" section of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'', being spelled ''Corellia Times'' as well as ''Corellian Times''.<ref name="GNN3" /><ref name="GNN7" /> The [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'' later expanded the history of the newspaper, using also both spellings.<ref name="SWG:ToOW" /><ref name="SWG:HVKItM" />

